00:36:24.180 --> 00:36:27.060
Yes, a question about the plotting pane.

00:36:27.060 --> 00:36:31.259
I see that you had a MATPLOTLIB plot up there.

00:36:31.259 --> 00:36:34.220
Do you support other plots or packages

00:36:34.220 --> 00:36:36.340
to C-borne plotly or anything like that?

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:40.120
Yep, the question was about Positron's plots pane

00:36:40.120 --> 00:36:43.479
and what sort of packages that we support.

00:36:43.479 --> 00:36:46.840
So we support MATPLOTLIB.

00:36:46.840 --> 00:36:49.579
Talking about modularity, most, actually,

00:36:49.579 --> 00:36:53.199
all Python plotting packages are built off of MATPLOTLIB.

00:36:53.199 --> 00:36:55.079
So we actually get a lot of support

00:36:55.079 --> 00:36:57.520
just from supporting MATPLOTLIB.

00:36:57.520 --> 00:36:59.359
But other packages that we know work well

00:36:59.359 --> 00:37:03.139
are plotly, C-borne, plot9.

00:37:03.139 --> 00:37:04.639
There's a whole bunch of others, but I

00:37:04.639 --> 00:37:06.560
think that's kind of the main ones

00:37:06.560 --> 00:37:08.079
that I can think of right now.

00:37:08.079 --> 00:37:11.159
So yes, many plots are supported.

00:37:11.159 --> 00:37:12.819
If you ever find one that isn't and you

00:37:12.819 --> 00:37:14.639
would like it to be, open a GitHub issue

00:37:14.639 --> 00:37:16.079
and we can support that for you.

