Thanks.

00:37:22.280 --> 00:37:25.039
You said that building for data scientists

00:37:25.039 --> 00:37:27.919
can be different than building for software engineers.

00:37:27.919 --> 00:37:29.379
There was a talk a couple of years

00:37:29.379 --> 00:37:32.079
back called, Why Software Engineers and Data Scientists

00:37:32.079 --> 00:37:34.440
Want to Murder Each Other.

00:37:34.479 --> 00:37:38.159
But when you're going from a tool user to a tool builder,

00:37:38.159 --> 00:37:42.400
you are shifting your own mindset from a data scientist

00:37:42.400 --> 00:37:47.720
why to a, or what, to an engineer's how.

00:37:47.720 --> 00:37:49.599
What's that shift like, and how are you

00:37:49.599 --> 00:37:51.280
able to make that work?

00:37:51.280 --> 00:37:53.240
Yeah.

00:37:53.240 --> 00:37:57.000
So the question is, when you go from data scientist

00:37:57.000 --> 00:38:00.079
to tool builder, these are, I talked about,

00:38:00.079 --> 00:38:01.879
they're two different skill sets.

00:38:01.879 --> 00:38:05.240
And how to make them happy together,

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:09.199
and how to live with the two wolves inside you, I suppose.

00:38:11.879 --> 00:38:14.599
I think a lot of what I think about

00:38:14.599 --> 00:38:17.159
is the empathy for the data scientist

00:38:17.159 --> 00:38:19.879
leaks into you as a software engineer.

00:38:19.879 --> 00:38:23.560
They are a very different tool, different ideas,

00:38:23.560 --> 00:38:26.960
different skills in some ways.

00:38:26.960 --> 00:38:30.440
So I think knowing what the outcome is is important.

00:38:30.440 --> 00:38:35.960
For example, I'm trying to think.

00:38:35.960 --> 00:38:39.079
Even like the plots pane, my data science brain

00:38:39.079 --> 00:38:41.720
says we should be able to iterate

00:38:41.720 --> 00:38:44.560
through all of these lines.

00:38:44.560 --> 00:38:46.479
But the software engineer part of my brain

00:38:46.479 --> 00:38:49.400
says, OK, when we're using plots in a notebook,

00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:51.000
oftentimes it's all one chunk.

00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:53.440
So how do we make sure that both of these work?

00:38:53.440 --> 00:38:55.720
So I think it's acknowledging that these

00:38:55.720 --> 00:38:59.800
are two different skills for software engineering

00:39:00.680 --> 00:39:02.159
A skill that I might be doing is I'm

00:39:02.159 --> 00:39:05.240
writing more end-to-end tests, or unit tests,

00:39:05.240 --> 00:39:08.400
or something like that, than I might as a data scientist.

00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:11.039
But having that empathy of knowing the problems to solve

00:39:11.039 --> 00:39:13.000
is super important.

00:39:13.000 --> 00:39:14.319
So thank you for that question.

